Tenor horn parts are written in the treble clef.

The tenor horn is an E♭ transposing instrument written a major sixth above concert pitch.

The tenor horn notation for middle C represents the E♭ below middle C in concert pitch (E♭3 in scientific pitch notation).


In music from Western culture, a sixth is a musical interval encompassing six note letter names or staff positions

The major sixth is one of two commonly occurring sixths.

It is qualified as major because it is the larger of the two.

The major sixth spans nine semitones. Its smaller counterpart, the minor sixth, spans eight semitones.